waits in Church Square for the start of the march.
Update, 4 July 2019 | CCMA response:
* The CCMA condemns Mr Nteke’s allegations as pure fabrication and absurd attack on our reputation. From our records, Mr Nteke does not have a case at the CCMA and he did not come forward to validate his allegation when requested. In addittion, Mr Nteke did not bother to use mechanisms put in place for reporting suspected corrupt conduct on the part of CCMA officials.
